                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12924830" author="ashutoshc" created="Tue, 26 Oct 2010 04:56:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;@Adam,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nice catch. Would you like to contribute a patch for it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12924972" author="awarring" created="Tue, 26 Oct 2010 15:06:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yea, I&apos;d like to do that. I&apos;ll try to get one up very soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007131" author="alexvk" created="Tue, 15 Mar 2011 20:00:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any update on this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13015533" author="awarring" created="Mon, 4 Apr 2011 19:27:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch that fixes the Header output by retrieving the information (the path, start offset, and length) from the FileSplit. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One potential issue with this code is that it has to gain a reference to the current MapContext, which it does from PigMapReduce.sJobContext, and if PIG is running in local mode, there may be a race condition. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1831&quot; title=&quot;Indeterministic behavior in local mode due to static variable PigMapReduce.sJobConf&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1831&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1831&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; solved a similar issue with the configuration. Would it be wise to use a thread local variable in PigMapReduce for the context as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13015571" author="awarring" created="Mon, 4 Apr 2011 20:42:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Review request can be found here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/547/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/547/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050037" author="olgan" created="Wed, 15 Jun 2011 22:17:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Delaying till 10 since we are about to spin the release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can one of the committers review post 0.9? thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050824" author="daijy" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 01:19:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks fine. Will commit it shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050826" author="daijy" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 01:24:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to trunk. Thanks Adam!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
